<br>
Am I a whiner ? Yes and no. I do NOT think that the skald class need a major overhaul, and that going to far has the risk to overpower it. Skalds are not gimped, however, they are below average. Not by much, but they are.<br>
And it is what, sometimes infuriates me. Because the skald class don't really need much effort, much rethinking to make it pefectly balanced and fun for all, there is no reason why we shouldn't, at last, got looked at. But just because Mythic (and the community to some extent) has adopted a &quot;skalds are fine&quot; hard line, those simple tweaks (mainly : alleviating skald &quot;redundancy&quot;, viable ranges and values for support songs, and something that can make us useful in sieges/defenses) won't be done ... unless it happens to be linked with another class change. Let's just look at how easily our shouts costs and regen song got fixed just because Minstrels got, at least, a deep and thorough revamp.<br>
<br>
