<br>
1.  I noticed that the lvl 8 and lvl 16 Chants Of Warding have the exact same effects but the lvl 16 has a higher power usage.<br>
<br>
2.  I know I'm biased <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , but I feel that the Reflection chant is much more powerful than the Warding chant, yet you wouldn't think so if you compared their power usage.  Maybe switch them?<br>
<br>
3.  Haste Shout -- I wish it could be group based instead of just self, but I know that could be stepping on Healer toes.  Without a shaman, you'd be OOE in 5 seconds flat...but with a shaman, it's a great way to pop PBT and get some good frontloaded dmg.<br>
<br>
<br>
4.  Damage Shield Chant -- Just an opinion...I die to casters 95% of the time, a dmg shield doesn't help that.  <br>
<br>
Regarding the RA changes.  I really like them all.  However, Pandemonium seems rather expensive for something that can be resisted, partially resisted, or purged all together and only lasts a max of 30 seconds.  If someone has 26% spirit resist, the spell will only last 22 seconds and then can't be used again for 15 mins.  I know most of the runie debuffs last a full minute and they are baseline spells (not even specline).  I suggest lowering the cost or increasing the spell duration.<br>
<br>
Thanks for taking all the time to put this together Rosey...I hope Mythic can keep an open mind.  Great Work!!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
