<br>
Theurgists completely throw Epic PvE encounters completely off scale by adding dozens or so attackers each to the to-hit equation when combined with a necromancer.<br>
<br>
Skalds were recently gimped in Epic PvE due to the massive nerf to damage adds.  I used to be able to do 4 +46 damage to a mob like legion, now I only do about 14+14.  Considering the damage add is our only support ability used in RvR, increasing the DPS of our shouts is just compensation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lxaell>l Xael l</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/3/03 12:24:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvE balance.</span><hr size=1> Well, I hope something happens for skalds, we sure need some attention.<br>
<br>
Taking weapon to 50 just to smooth out variance isn't a good way of looking at it. Even with the 100-125% damage being 50 spec (natural or with items), most of us still hit for sub-par damage. If we're generally looked at as the melee support class, for the love of Bragi tweak our melee damage. <br>
<br>
I support most of the changes (I'd like to see it be a group haste with 1500 range), but for most its too little too late. No respecs means you have to play with a sub-par spec in the hopes of your realm defeating the dragon. Then hoping and praying you win a respec stone. Just not an option for most, if not all of us.<br>
<br>
Right now, I'm specced 46 axe 43 bs 2 parry... and am considering leaving points unspent and hope for the best. Given Mythic's track record, I don't expect any love soon... although it would be nice.<br>
